<http://globonews.globo.com/GloboNews/article/0,6993,A549912-2430,00.html>

Brazil - Bahia state: 55 dengue cases confirmed
-----------------------------------------------
Fifty-five cases of dengue fever were confirmed by the Central Laboratory.
They had previously been diagnosed as typhoid, but all tested negative for
typhoid.
******
[6]
Date: Sun 8 Jun 2003
From: Marilda Milagres <milagres@fclnet.com.br>
Source: Informativo Globo News, Sat 7 Jun 2003 [in Portuguese, summary by
Mod.JW]
<http://goiasnet.globo.com/ultimas/ult_report.phtm?cod=99702>

Brazil - Ceara state: 177 DHF cases and 12 deaths
-------------------------------------------------
Ceara has had 14 214 cases of dengue confirmed in 2003, according to the 7
Jun 2003 bulletin by the state health secretary. This is almost equal to
the total registered in 2002. There were 1063 cases in just one week; 30
per cent of the cases were in the capital, Fortaleza, with 4309 confirmed
cases, 605 more than the previous week´s cumulative total. There have been
177 cases of dengue hemorrhagic fever (DHF), with 12 deaths.
--
Marilda Milagres
<milagres@fclnet.com.br>
