[7]
Date: Wed 11 Jun 2003
From: "Pablo Nart" <p.nart@virgin.net>
Source: La Nacion, Costa Rica, 11 Jun 2003 [In Spanish, translated and
summarized by Mod.JW]
<http://www.nacion.co.cr/ln_ee/2003/junio/11/pais10.html>

Costa Rica: 2163 cases reported this year
-----------------------------------------
Up to Sat 7 Jun 2003 the Ministry of Health has reported 2163 cases of
dengue in Costa Rica, most in Guanacaste (44 per cent) and Puntarenas (35
per cent), according to the director of epidemiological surveillance of the
Ministry of Health, Teresita Solano.
Dengue returned to the country in 1993 and has since caused 2 large
epidemics, the largest in 1997 with 14 000 cases.
******
[8])
Date: Mon 16 Jun 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Pan American Health Organization (PAHO) website, June 2003
<http://www.paho.org/default.htm>

Cumulative dengue statistics for the Americas 2003
--------------------------------------------------
According to the information reported to PAHO up to 3 Jun 2003 the
serotypes of the dengue viruses (DENV) associated with DHF cases in Brazil
and Costa Rica are as follows:
Brazil -- DENV 1, DENV 2, and DENV 3;
Costa Rica -- DENV 1.
The cumulative data for the year 2003 up to 3 Jun 2003 can be accessed at
<http://www.paho.org/english/HCP/HCT/VBD/dengue-cases-2003.htm>.
The corresponding data for earlier years can be accessed through the PAHO
website: <http://www.paho.org/english/HCP/HCT/VBD/dengue.htm>.
